SIMPLE: retrospect
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retrospect
<hw>Re"tro*spect</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>retrospicere</ets>; <ets>retro</ets> back + <ets>specere</ets>,
<ets>spectum</ets>, to look. See <er>Spy</er>, <ets>and cf</ets>.
<er>Expect</er>.]</ety> <def>To look backward; hence, to affect or
concern what is past.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It may be useful to <qex>retrospect</qex> to an early period.</q>
<rj><qau>A. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrospect</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Retrospect
<hw>Re"tro*spect</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A looking back on things past;
view or contemplation of the past.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We may introduce a song without <qex>retrospect</qex> to the old
comedy.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrospection</ent>⟦br⟧
